<br>
Its funny the way son George's enthusiasm is the exact reverse of his father's.<br>
<br>
Noticable in his book (where G.D. could control the presentation), it is most direct in the trancript of the radio program made during the promotional tour, where Freeman - who actually knows what he is talking about - repeatedly disagreed with George.<br>
